Hibiscus es un género de plantas con flores in the mallow familia, Malvaceae (familia de la malva). The género is quite grande, comprising varios cientos de especies that are nativo de warm templado, subtropical and tropical regiones throughout the world. their grande, vistoso flores and those especie are comúnmente conocido simply as "hibiscus", or less widely known as rose mallow. The género incluye both anual and perenne herbáceo plants, as well as leñoso arbustos and pequeño árboles.

Several especie are ampliamente cultivado as plantas ornamentales, notably Hibiscus syriacus and Hibiscus × rosa-sinensis. The generic name is derived from the Greek name ἰβίσκος (ibískos) which Greek botanist Pedanius Dioscorides gave to a plant now scientifically labelled as Althaea officinalis. The hojas are alterno, ovalado to lanceolado, often with a dentado or lobulado margen (dentate). The flores are grande and conspicuo. They are forma de trompeta, with five or more pétalos, colour from blanco to rosa, rojo, azul, naranja, durazno, amarillo or púrpura, and from 4–18 cm ancho.

**Fuente:** 

Baccharis /ˈbækərɪs/ es un género de perennials and arbustos in the aster familia (Asteraceae (familia del girasol)). They are comúnmente conocido as baccharises but sometimes referred to as "brooms", because many members have pequeño thin hojas resembling the true brooms. They are not at all related to these however, but belong to an entirely different lineage of eudicots. B. halimifolia is comúnmente conocido as "groundsel bush", however true groundsels are encontrado en the género Senecio.

Baccharis, with over 500 especie, is one of the largest genera in the Asteraceae (familia del girasol). It is found throughout the América, distribuido mainly in the warmer regiones of Brasil, Argentina, Colombia, Chile and México, with B. halimifolia ranging northward along the Atlántico costa to the sur tip of Nova Scotia in Canada. If present, the hojas of Baccharis are borne along the stems in alterno fashion. flores are usually blanco or pinkish. There are no ray flores, but many disk flores which are either staminate or pistillate. algunas especies of Baccharis are toxic to animals; in particular, consumption of B. coridifolia may lead to necrosis in the gastrointestinal tract of cattle, horses, sheep, and rabbits.

Eugenia es un género de plantas con flores in the myrtle familia Myrtaceae (familia del mirto). It has a worldwide, although highly uneven, distribution in tropical and subtropical regiones. The bulk of the aproximadamente 1,100 especie occur in the New World tropics, especially in the este Brasil's norte Andes, the Caribe, and the Atlántico Forest (costero forests). Other centers of diversity include New Caledonia and Madagascar. muchas especies in the Old World have received a new clasificación into the género Syzygium.

All especie are leñoso perenne árboles and arbustos. Several are cultivado como plantas ornamentales for their atractivo brillante follaje, and a few produce edible fruto that are eaten fresh or used in jams and jellies. The género was named in honor of Prince Eugene of Savoy. and are in the process of being described from these regiones. For example, 37 new especie of Eugenia have been described from Mesoamerica in the past few years. being described from New Caledonia, and new to science may occur in Madagascar. of the myrtle familia in Australia (e.g. Eucalyptus, Corymbia, Angophora, Melaleuca, Callistemon, Rhodamnia, Gossia), only one especie of Eugenia, E. reinwardtiana, occurs on that continent. The género also is represented in Africa south of the Sahara, but it is relatively especie-poor on that continent. in the honeysuckle familia Caprifoliaceae.

The member especie are perenne or caducifolio arbustos or (in a few cases) pequeño árboles nativo throughout the templado norte Hemisphere, with a few especie extendiéndose into tropical montane regiones in Sudamérica and southeast Asia. In Africa, the género is confined to the Atlas Mountains. , in which it referred to V. lantana. The hojas are opuesto, simple, and entero, with dentado or lobulado margins. Cool templado especie are caducifolio, while most of the warm templado especie are perenne. algunas especies have densely hairy shoots and hojas covered in star-shaped hairs.

**Fuente:** 

Cordia es un género de plantas con flores in the borage familia, Boraginaceae (familia de la borraja). It contiene 228 especie of arbustos and árboles, that are encontrado en tropical and subtropical regiones worldwide. Many of the especie are commonly called manjack, while bocote may refer to several Central American especie in Spanish.

The generic name honours German botanist and pharmacist Valerius Cordus (1515–1544). Like most other Boraginaceae (familia de la borraja), the majority have trichomes (hairs) on the hojas. The taxonomía of Cordia is complex and controversial. Gottschling et al. (2005) say this is partly due to "extraordinarily high intraspecific variability" in some groups of especie, making identification difficult, and partly due to new taxa having been "airily described on the basis of poorly preserved herbarium specimens". Cordia especie are usado como food plants by the caterpillars of some Lepidoptera especie, such as Endoclita malabaricus, Bucculatrix caribbea, and Bucculatrix cordiaella. The wild olive tortoise beetle (Physonota alutacea) feeds on C. boissieri, C. dentata, C. inermis, and C. macrostachya.

Several especie formerly placed in this género (such as those used to prepare the psychotomimetic snuffs vilca and yopo/parica) are now considered to be in the género Anadenanthera. Three especie have also been placed in género Adenopodia. Others have been moved to the género Pityrocarpa.
